{{ 'dev-policy.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

{%- comment -%} Fixed design tokens from Figma — not merchant-controlled {%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  .dev-policy {
    --font-body: 'Public Sans', sans-serif;
    --font-heading: 'Test Tiempos Headline', serif;

    /* Desktop/Title 3 for the card, Desktop/Title 4 for a question. Mobile states its own
       sizes on the artboard, so they win over a scale factor. */
    --font-title-size: 32px;
    --font-title-size-mobile: 24px;
    --font-qa-size: 22px;
    --font-qa-size-mobile: 20px;
    --font-heading-weight: 500;
    --font-heading-lh: 1.2;

    /* The card's own copy is Body/Lg (18); a question's answer is Body/Md (16). */
    --font-card-body-size: 18px;
    --font-qa-body-size: 16px;
    --font-body-weight: 500;
    --font-body-lh: 1.4;

    --card-radius: 32px;
    --card-pad: 32px;
    --card-pad-mobile: 24px;
    --card-gap: 16px;

    --qa-item-gap: 8px;
    --note-pt: 24px;

    /* Split (Delivery & Returns, 45246:3564).

       Fluid, not stepped. A single breakpoint at 1024 left 1025–1200 holding the full 533px card
       AND the full 136px gutter, which squeezed the answers to ~228px at 1025 — the worst point on
       the whole curve sat just ABOVE the breakpoint meant to fix it. The vw terms are the artboard
       ratios (64/1440, 136/1440, 533/1440), so at 1440 they resolve to exactly 64 / 136 / 533 and
       the pixel reference is untouched; below that everything scales together instead of the
       answers absorbing the entire loss. */
    --section-px: clamp(24px, 4.4444vw, 64px);
    --section-py: 40px;
    --col-gap: clamp(40px, 9.4444vw, 136px);
    --card-w: clamp(280px, 37.0139vw, 533px);
    --qa-gap: 24px;

    /* Centered (Shipping policy, 45246:4418). Figma states px-[400px] at 1440, which is a
       640px column dead-centre — expressed as a max-width so it survives narrower viewports. */
    --centered-max: 640px;
    --centered-py: 24px;
    --centered-gap: 32px;
    --qa-gap-centered: 32px;

    --section-px-mobile: 16px;
    --section-py-mobile: 16px;
    --qa-gap-mobile: 24px;
  }
</style>

{%- liquid
  assign qa_blocks = section.blocks | where: 'type', 'qa'
  assign note_blocks = section.blocks | where: 'type', 'note'
  assign layout_class = 'dev-policy--' | append: section.settings.layout
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  Delivery & Returns and Shipping policy are the same section in two layouts:

    split    — a cream card on the left (heading + copy, sticky as you scroll the answers)
               and the Q&A column on the right.  45246:3564
    centered — a cream banner with a centred heading and the Q&A stacked under it in a
               640px column.  45246:4418

  On mobile the two collapse into ONE layout: the card becomes a full-width banner with the
  heading centred, the Q&A stacks below it, and the card's body copy is dropped entirely —
  the mobile Delivery artboard (45246:1161) simply does not carry it.

  Every class is dev-prefixed: Horizon compiles every stock section's {% stylesheet %} into a
  sheet that loads on every page, so an unprefixed BEM name inherits stock rules.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div
  class="dev-policy {{ layout_class }}"
  style="
    --bg: {{ section.settings.background_color }};
    --color: {{ section.settings.text_color }};
    --card-bg: {{ section.settings.card_color }};
    --pt: {{ section.settings.padding_top }}px;
    --pb: {{ section.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
  "
>
  <div class="dev-policy__inner">
    <div class="dev-policy__card">
      {%- if section.settings.title != blank -%}
        {%- comment -%} inline_richtext: already safe HTML from Shopify — never escape it. {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          <h1>, not <h2>. This section IS the page's main content — the page templates render no
          title of their own, so before this the whole document had no h1 at all and its outline
          opened at level 2. The children below are h2 for the same reason: an h1 followed by an h3
          is a skipped level.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <h1 class="dev-policy__title">{{ section.settings.title }}</h1>
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- if section.settings.body != blank -%}
        <div class="dev-policy__card-body">{{ section.settings.body }}</div>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    {%- if qa_blocks.size > 0 or note_blocks.size > 0 -%}
      <div class="dev-policy__list">
        {%- for block in qa_blocks -%}
          <div class="dev-policy__item" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
            {%- if block.settings.heading != blank -%}
              <h2 class="dev-policy__question">{{ block.settings.heading }}</h2>
            {%- endif -%}
            {%- if block.settings.body != blank -%}
              <div class="dev-policy__answer">{{ block.settings.body }}</div>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        {%- endfor -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          The "Still got questions?" group. Same shape as a question, but Figma pads it 24px away
          from the list above (45246:3617), so it is its own block type rather than a styling flag.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- for block in note_blocks -%}
          <div class="dev-policy__item dev-policy__item--note" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
            {%- if block.settings.heading != blank -%}
              <h2 class="dev-policy__question">{{ block.settings.heading }}</h2>
            {%- endif -%}
            {%- if block.settings.body != blank -%}
              <div class="dev-policy__answer">{{ block.settings.body }}</div>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Policy",
  "tag": "section",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "header", "content": "Content" },
    { "type": "inline_richtext", "id": "title", "label": "Title", "default": "Delivery & Returns" },
    { "type": "richtext", "id": "body", "label": "Intro copy", "info": "Shown beside the questions on desktop in the Split layout. Not shown on mobile, and not shown in the Centered layout — neither artboard carries it." },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Layout" },
    {
      "type": "select",
      "id": "layout",
      "label": "Layout",
      "default": "split",
      "options": [
        { "value": "split", "label": "Split — card left, questions right" },
        { "value": "centered", "label": "Centered — banner above, questions below" }
      ]
    },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Colors" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "background_color", "label": "Background", "default": "#FFFCF4" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "text_color", "label": "Text color", "default": "#333333" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "card_color", "label": "Card background", "default": "#FCF5E3" },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Spacing" },
    { "type": "range", "id": "padding_top", "min": 0, "max": 120, "step": 4, "unit": "px", "label": "Padding top", "default": 0 },
    { "type": "range", "id": "padding_bottom", "min": 0, "max": 120, "step": 4, "unit": "px", "label": "Padding bottom", "default": 0 }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "qa",
      "name": "Question",
      "settings": [
        { "type": "inline_richtext", "id": "heading", "label": "Question", "default": "How much does delivery cost?" },
        { "type": "richtext", "id": "body", "label": "Answer", "default": "<p>We offer free standard delivery to all UK addresses.</p>" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "name": "Closing note",
      "limit": 1,
      "settings": [
        { "type": "inline_richtext", "id": "heading", "label": "Heading", "default": "Still got questions?" },
        { "type": "richtext", "id": "body", "label": "Text", "default": "<p><strong>Click here</strong> to chat with us</p>" }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Policy",
      "blocks": [
        { "type": "qa" },
        { "type": "note" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
